Class DateTimeParser

All Implemented Interfaces:
DataParser
public class DateTimeParser
extends DateParser

DataParser instance that parses Date values as java.util.Date instances, representing a particular date and time. This class uses a backing DateFormat instance to perform parsing. The DateFormat instance to use can be passed in to the constructor, or by default the DateFormat returned by DateFormat.getDateTimeInstance(int, int) with both arguments being DateFormat.SHORT is used.
